			<div class="comment-content"><p>Hey Andy, </p>
<p>Really glad you liked the project and have built one. The red LED&#8217;s look great! I wish I had bought the dual colour displays now so I could have a menu option to switch colours.</p>
<p>As for the DS1307. The pinout I have is 5 and 6 to Arduino, 7 is N/C and 8 goes to +5v. Pin 8 is bottom right on my photo.<br />
See the chip pinout here: <a href="http://www.datasheetdir.com/DS1307+Real-Time-Clocks-RTC" rel="nofollow">http://www.datasheetdir.com/DS1307+Real-Time-Clocks-RTC</a>. </p>
<p>Cheers<br />
Nick</p>
</div>

