			<div class="comment-content"><p>It&#8217;s nice to hear you managed to get rid of the gap. I would like to see your solution.</p>
<p>From what I imagine, the change in the code consists in talking to 4 different HT1632 chips (each controlling a 0832 display) rather than just one (controlling the 2416 display). You will have one CS line to each of the 0832 displays (whose address also needs to be set, with the switches).<br />
A bit of work, but not &#8220;rocket science&#8221; as they say :)</p>
</div>

