	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 highlander-comment" id="li-comment-259">
		<article id="comment-259" class="comment">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
					<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/bf8dc7ec2876168709cd70a41ae19d8b?s=68&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=G' class='avatar avatar-68' height='68' width='68' /><span class="fn"><a href='http://timewitharduino.blogspot.com/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>FlorinC</a></span> on <a href="http://123led.wordpress.com/about/#comment-259"><time datetime="2011-06-20T20:55:12+00:00">June 20, 2011 at 20:55</time></a> <span class="says">said:</span>
									</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->

				
			</footer>

			<div class="comment-content"><p>Not bad, for a first, blind, try.<br />
It seems that displays 1 and 2 are accessed correctly.<br />
In function displayScrollingLine, you need to make some changes. I left the second param as 0, but it should have been really &#8220;y&#8221;, and its value, set at the top of the same function, should be between 0 (top of the screen) and 10 (let&#8217;s say).</p>
<p>    ht1632_putchar(-x+6,  0, ((crtPos+1 &lt; strlen(msg)) ? msg[crtPos+1] : &#039; &#039;));<br />
should be<br />
    ht1632_putchar(-x+6,  y, ((crtPos+1 &lt; strlen(msg)) ? msg[crtPos+1] : &#039; &#039;));</p>
<p>etc (same for the rest of the line).<br />
I think you got the idea.</p>
</div>

			<div class="reply">
				<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/about/?replytocom=259#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-259", "259", "respond", "2")'>Reply <span>&darr;</span></a>			</div><!-- .reply -->
