	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 highlander-comment" id="li-comment-261">
		<article id="comment-261" class="comment">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
					<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/339147b588cbc52f1293005a9f4d5850?s=68&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=G' class='avatar avatar-68' height='68' width='68' /><span class="fn">Sven</span> on <a href="http://123led.wordpress.com/about/#comment-261"><time datetime="2011-06-21T16:17:10+00:00">June 21, 2011 at 16:17</time></a> <span class="says">said:</span>
									</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->

				
			</footer>

			<div class="comment-content"><p>Hi Florin !</p>
<p>I changed the code to this here  :</p>
<p>void displayScrollingLine()<br />
{<br />
  // modify this value to display the text on the desired display row;<br />
  int y = 4;</p>
<p>  // shift the whole screen 6 times, one column at a time;<br />
  for (int x=0; x &lt; 6; x++)<br />
  {<br />
    ht1632_putchar(-x, 0, msg[crtPos]);<br />
    ht1632_putchar(-x+6,  y, ((crtPos+1 &lt; strlen(msg)) ? msg[crtPos+1] : &#039; &#039;));<br />
    ht1632_putchar(-x+12, y, ((crtPos+2 &lt; strlen(msg)) ? msg[crtPos+2] : &#039; &#039;));<br />
    ht1632_putchar(-x+18, y, ((crtPos+3 &lt; strlen(msg)) ? msg[crtPos+3] : &#039; &#039;));<br />
    ht1632_putchar(-x+24, y, ((crtPos+4 &lt; strlen(msg)) ? msg[crtPos+4] : &#039; &#039;));<br />
    ht1632_putchar(-x+30, y, ((crtPos+5 &lt; strlen(msg)) ? msg[crtPos+5] : &#039; &#039;));<br />
    ht1632_putchar(-x+36, y, ((crtPos+6 = strlen(msg))<br />
  {<br />
    crtPos = 0;<br />
  }<br />
}</p>
<p>Again a link what it looks like :<br />
<a href="http://imageshack.us/clip/my-videos/696/uavt.mp4/" rel="nofollow">http://imageshack.us/clip/my-videos/696/uavt.mp4/</a></p>
<p>I will put the displays back together again&#8230; it´s not nice this here :-)</p>
<p>From wednesday  till sunday I am not able to test because I do a little trip&#8230;</p>
<p>But I will be online if there is any question !!</p>
<p>THANKS !!!</p>
</div>

