	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 highlander-comment" id="li-comment-263">
		<article id="comment-263" class="comment">
			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
					<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/bf8dc7ec2876168709cd70a41ae19d8b?s=68&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=G' class='avatar avatar-68' height='68' width='68' /><span class="fn"><a href='http://timewitharduino.blogspot.com/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>FlorinC</a></span> on <a href="http://123led.wordpress.com/about/#comment-263"><time datetime="2011-06-21T21:08:24+00:00">June 21, 2011 at 21:08</time></a> <span class="says">said:</span>
									</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->

				
			</footer>

			<div class="comment-content"><p>Sven,<br />
It look good to me. In principle, it works.<br />
Now, do the following 2 steps:<br />
1. insert these 2 lines somewhere in the file (close to the top):</p>
<p>#define fWriteA(_pin_, _state_) ( _pin_ &lt; 8 ? (_state_ ?  PORTD |= 1 &lt;&lt; _pin_ : \<br />
PORTD &amp;= ~(1 &lt;&lt; _pin_ )) : (_state_ ?  PORTB |= 1 &lt;&lt; (_pin_ -8) : PORTB &amp;= ~(1 &lt;&lt; (_pin_ -8)  )))</p>
<p>2. replace &quot;digitalWrite&quot; everywhere with &quot;fWriteA&quot; (arguments to the function will stay the same).<br />
This should speed things a bit.</p>
</div>

