			<div class="comment-content"><p>Hi Don,</p>
<p>Glad you like it. I don&#8217;t have any code to hand, your best bet would be to adapt the code that&#8217;s in the pongclock sketch itself. The display you mention looks to have the same controller chip, so it should work with the driver functions. You would need to obviously change where stuff was drawn on screen to fit the new display&#8217;s resolution of 32&#215;8.</p>
<p>If you just wanted a bigger clock, Sure do a bigger version of the 2416 boards that use 5mm LEDs. I know a few people have used those with this sketch.</p>
<p>Cheers<br />
Nick</p>
</div>

