					<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/86b77e4f66a277fad74763ee5dcdb2d4?s=39&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=G' class='avatar avatar-39' height='39' width='39' /><span class="fn">Nick</span> on <a href="http://123led.wordpress.com/about/#comment-5652"><time datetime="2012-04-09T11:26:29+00:00">April 9, 2012 at 11:26</time></a> <span class="says">said:</span>
									</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->

				
			</footer>

			<div class="comment-content"><p>Hey Matthew, </p>
<p>Yeah unfortunately it would be quite a lot of work to adapt the code &#8211; e.g.</p>
<p>- rewrite the driver code to address 1 display not two, and to write in the correct format for that bi-colour display<br />
- rewrite the clock modes to support the reduced 32 pixel width (the 2 displays I use give 48 pixels)<br />
- redesign the fonts to fit 32 width &#8211; i don&#8217;t think the big numbers will fit.<br />
- add in any customisations you wanted to make it bi colour.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s di-able (apart from word mode which might not fit on 32 pixels) but quite a big re write.</p>
<p>Cheers<br />
Nick</p>
</div>

