			<div class="comment-content"><p>Hi, I saw this project and I wanted to have one! Just ordered the parts in China via american and british ebay, have them delivered to Germany within 4 weeks, and built the thing. Great! Everything works fine, but&#8230;<br />
When I looked inside the code, I found at least two recursions, which are a NoGo in embedded programming:<br />
Function normal_clock() calls itself in line 487, function pong() calls itself in line 797.<br />
I have not analyzed further, but maybe you will get a stack-overflow when you press the button continously.<br />
void normal_clock(){ &#8230;<br />
if(buttonB.uniquePress()){<br />
&#8230;<br />
    normal_clock();<br />
    return;<br />
}<br />
Do I see this correct? Or is there something special in C for Arduino, which I did not understand?</p>
</div>

