			<footer class="comment-meta">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
					<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/86b77e4f66a277fad74763ee5dcdb2d4?s=39&#038;d=identicon&#038;r=G' class='avatar avatar-39' height='39' width='39' /><span class="fn">Nick</span> on <a href="http://123led.wordpress.com/about/#comment-18085"><time datetime="2013-06-16T10:45:13+00:00">June 16, 2013 at 10:45</time></a> <span class="says">said:</span>
									</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->

				
			</footer>

			<div class="comment-content"><p>Hey, </p>
<p>This is all very strange, I&#8217;ve never seen this behaviour. Everything should just work, you shouldn&#8217;t have to start changing odd things in the code per mode. If the time data is correct they should all be fine.</p>
<p>It sounds like you have a bigger issue, maybe an unstable power supply? Does it work without the displays plugged in and some debug lines, or with just one plugged in? Try and reduce the power draw. Are you powering via USB? </p>
<p>Do you another Arduino to test it with?</p>
<p>Nick</p>
</div>

