			<div class="comment-content"><p>I&#8217;m discovering this exciting project! Very thank you to you to share your work.</p>
<p>I wonder if you know about the real power consumption. Of course it depends of how many leds are on at a certain moment but we can measure an average and a peak. According to the specs, I though about something like 50 mA for the Arduino and 100 mA for each led panel. But you talk about a power supply of 150 mA, is it really enough? </p>
<p>My idea is to supply power with batteries.</p>
<p>Regads,<br />
Matock</p>
